### Finding 16: No data export or deletion capability (GDPR)

**What's happening:**

If a European user requests their data (GDPR Article 15 — Right of Access) or asks you to delete their account (Article 17 — Right to Erasure), you have **no mechanism** to do either. There's no "Download My Data" button, no "Delete Account" button, and no admin tool for it.

**Why it's dangerous:**

GDPR non-compliance fines can be up to €20 million or 4% of annual revenue (whichever is higher). Even if you're a small app, a user complaint to a data protection authority could trigger an investigation.

**Severity:** 🟡 **MEDIUM** (legal risk, not technical)

**Fix — add a delete account function:**

```js
// authService.js — add this function
deleteAccount: async (userId) => {
  // 1. Delete all user's prompts
  await supabase.from('prompts').delete().eq('created_by', userId);

  // 2. Delete avatar from storage
  await supabase.storage.from('avatars').remove([`${userId}.webp`]);

  // 3. Delete profile
  await supabase.from('profiles').delete().eq('id', userId);

  // 4. Sign out (clears session)
  await supabase.auth.signOut();

  // Note: Deleting from auth.users requires the service_role key
  // Do this via a Supabase Edge Function or Dashboard
},
```

Add a "Delete My Account" button to Profile.jsx with a confirmation dialog.

